<doc id="627413" wikidata="Q6247343" url="?curid=627413" title="John Maynard Smith Prize">
<text>The John Maynard Smith Prize is a prize given by the European Society for Evolutionary Biology on odd years to an outstanding young researcher. It was first awarded in 1997 and is named after the evolutionary biologist John Maynard Smith (1920–2004).

==List of winners==
Source: European Society for Evolutionary Biology
