<doc id="627623" wikidata="Q1171125" url="?curid=627623" title="Compound spirit of ether">
<text>Compound spirit of ether, also called Hoffmann&#x27;s anodyne, Hoffmann&#x27;s drops, or aetheris spiritus compositus, is a solution of one part diethyl ether in three parts alcohol. It is used traditionally as an anodyne or as a hypnotic. Its use as a drug was introduced by Friedrich Hoffmann.

